1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. g3 dxc4 5. Qa4+ {is harmless} Bd7 {this is more 
straight-forward than the more popular alternative Nbd7 as it resolves the problem of 
the light-squared bishopimmediately} 6. Qxc4 Bc6 7. Bg2 Nbd7 8. O-O {is too automatic 
and allows black easy play} Bd5 9. Qc2 Be4 10. Qd1 c5 $11 {black already equalised, 
the bishop is active on e4 and he also managed to push ...c5} 11. Nc3 Bc6 12. Qd3 Qb6 
13. Be3 Rd8 {and the queen is uncomfortable on d3} *

