1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. g3 dxc4 5. Qa4+ {is harmless} Bd7 {this is more 
straight-forward than the more popular alternative Nbd7 as it resolves the problem of 
the light-squared bishopimmediately} 6. Qxc4 Bc6 7. Bg2 Nbd7 8. Nc3 {this is more 
critical, white fights for the e4-square immediately} Nb6 9. Qd3 Bb4 {black also 
fights for control of the e4-square} 10. O-O O-O 11. Bg5 h6 12. Bxf6 {a typical 
exchange in the Catalan, giving the bishop pair in order to establish a strong 
centre.} Qxf6 13. Ne4 Bxe4 14. Qxe4 c6 $11 *

