ago. Black wants to solve the problem with the Bc8 so white's next move is 
practically forced if he wants to fight for an advantage.} 6. Nbd2 Bc6 7. Nxc4 Bd5 8. 
Ne3 Bb4+ 9. Bd2 Bxd2+ 10. Qxd2 O-O 11. Nxd5 exd5 12. Qb4 Qc8 {with ...c6 to follow 
with an excellent position for black - the Bg2 is not on the best square in this 
Carlsbad structure} *

