castle, but white had better chances for an attack even though the positions were 
usuallydouble-edged. The rook move aims for active play in the centre by ...e5.} 10. 
Nc3 Be7 11. Qa4 Nb4 $1 {this typical reaction to Qa4 does the trick again} 12. Qxa7 
O-O 13. Qxb7 Nfd5 14. a3 Rb8 $11 {with repetition} 15. Qa7 Ra8 16. Qb7 Rab8 $11 {with 
repetition} *

