1. d4 d5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. Bf4 c5 {more likely than not this will transpose to the main 
line. There are only a couple of minor options when white can play differently and 
these are analysed here.} 4. e3 Nc6 5. c3 cxd4 6. exd4 Bf5 7. Qb3 Qc8 8. Na3 {a 
recent attempt by Harikrishna} a6 {preventing Nb5} 9. Nh4 {these knights on the rim 
do not leave a good impression and you will see in some of the lines below that they 
only bring trouble to white.} Be4 10. f3 Bg6 11. Nxg6 hxg6 12. g4 {is better, to 
prevent black's next} e6 13. Nc2 Qd7 14. h4 Bd6 $1 15. Bxd6 Qxd6 {and black is more 
than OK, as the awkward Nc2 has no perspective and white cannot take on b7} 16. Qxb7 
$2 O-O 17. Qb3 Rfb8 18. Qa3 Qg3+ 19. Ke2 e5 $19 {with a winning attack} *

