1. d4 d5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. Bf4 c5 {more likely than not this will transpose to the main 
line. There are only a couple of minor options when white can play differently and 
these are analysed here.} 4. c3 Nc6 5. dxc5 {the only independent try, but it's 
dubious. White advances with the pawns too early and they can only be attacked by 
black later on. The following shows that black has easy play which can quickly become 
an advantage.} e6 6. b4 a5 7. Nd4 axb4 8. Nxc6 bxc6 9. cxb4 Ng4 $1 {an important 
move, the threat is ...Qf6, hitting the Bf4 and Ra1} 10. Qd4 Be7 11. Qxg7 Bf6 12. 
Qxg4 e5 $19 {is devastating} 13. Qf3 exf4 14. Nc3 Ra3 $19 *

