1. d4 d5 2. Bf4 {this has become the more popular move order lately, but in our case 
it doesn't make a difference because even after 2 Nf3 Nf6 3 Bf4 we're headed towards 
the 'tabiya' that arises after black's 8th move. This is very convenient for black as 
he can concentrate on studying the tabiya - it will arise in the vast majority of 
times and the alternatives are few and give him good play.} Nf6 3. e3 c5 4. Nc3 $5 
{is an unaesthetic move that was recently tried by Carlsen and previously by Jobava 
and Rapport. It needs to be taken seriously, especially when white treats it in an 
aggressive manner.} cxd4 5. exd4 a6 6. Nf3 Nc6 {this is safer than the typical Bg4, 
which after 7 h3 Bf3 8 Qf3 e6 allows 9 g4 when white's attack is rather annoying.} 7. 
Be2 Bf5 $11 {is problem-free for black} *

