{is an unaesthetic move that was recently tried by Carlsen and previously by Jobava 
and Rapport. It needs to be taken seriously, especially when white treats it in an 
aggressive manner.} cxd4 5. exd4 a6 6. Nf3 Nc6 {this is safer than the typical Bg4, 
which after 7 h3 Bf3 8 Qf3 e6 allows 9 g4 when white's attack is rather annoying.} 7. 
Ne5 {the only move to pose problems} Bd7 8. Be2 e6 9. O-O Qb6 10. Nxc6 Bxc6 11. Rb1 
Be7 {black has no problems here} 12. Bf3 O-O 13. Ne2 Rfc8 14. Re1 Ba4 15. Nc3 Bc6 16. 
Ne2 Ba4 17. Nc3 Bc6 18. Ne2 {1/2-1/2 (18) Kovalev,V (2599) -L'Ami,E (2611) Baku 2016} 
*

