[SourceTitle "03 Trompowsky"]
[Source "Chessable.com"]
[Comment "on-the-way-to-the-queens-gambit-declined/course/4642, variation/151630"]

1. d4 d5 2. Bg5 {the Trompowsky isn't that effective when the knight is still on g8, 
but some Tromp die-hards like to play like this} h6 3. Bh4 c6 {black's plan is 
simple: he plays ...Qb6, develops the bishop on f5 and then plays ...e6 (or ...e5 in 
the lines when white delays Nf3) with easy play} 4. e3 {this allows black to push 
...e5 in view of the undefended Bh4} Qb6 5. b3 e5 6. Nf3 exd4 {this is simpler. e4 is 
also quite good, giving the position a more closed character. If you feel comfortable 
in those positions you can safely go ahead and play it!} 7. exd4 Bg4 8. c3 Be7 9. 
Bxe7 Nxe7 10. Bd3 O-O 11. O-O Nd7 {with equality} *

