e5 $1 18. d5 cxd5 19. cxd5 Rc5 {threatening to double on the c-file. The d5-pawn 
isn't dangerous as it's not going anywhere, while black's counterplay on the c-file 
and the queenside is just beginning. Now white's best advised to take the repetition 
after} 20. Na4 Ra5 21. Nc3 Rc5 $11 {while black can still play on if he wishes after 
Nc8 with the idea of ...Nd6} *

