10. Be2 O-O 11. O-O Rfc8 $1 {this is a nice move, anticipating white's c5 (which is 
his only plan in this position, to try to advance on the queenside) .} 12. c5 Qd8 13. 
b4 Nh5 $1 {without the strong Bg3 white's queenside play is harmless} 14. Be5 Nhf6 
{threatening to take on e5 without marooning the knight on h5} 15. Bg3 Nh5 $11 {with 
repetition. Black can continue if he wishes by playing a5, for example.} *

