1. d4 d5 2. Nc3 Nf6 3. Bf4 {Jobava's favourite, but not particularly threatening 
after black's next move} a6 $1 {cutting out ideas based on Nb5 and by securing b5 
black's natural development with ...c5 follow smoothly. In this line it's safer to 
keep the bishop on c8 as putting it on f5 invites some aggressive play by white after 
f3 and g4} 4. e3 e6 5. Bd3 c5 6. Nf3 Nc6 7. O-O c4 {it was possible to just develop, 
but this is more ambitious as black can get his queenside play rolling} 8. Be2 b5 9. 
Ne5 Bb7 10. Bf3 {0-1 (61) Darini,P (2511) -Fressinet,L (2672) Doha QAT 2016} b4 {an 
improvement over Fressinet's immediate Bd6 which allowed 11 e4. This kicks the Nc3 
and increases control over e4.} 11. Ne2 Bd6 {with good play for black} *

