f6, which some Veresov players like to do, but then black has excellent play} 4. Qd2 
Nbd7 5. f3 $6 h6 6. Bh4 e5 {if black can get ...e5 in these structures he is almost 
always better} 7. dxe5 Nxe5 8. e3 Ne4 $1 {the simplest; if black wants a more 
complicated game he can play Ng6 in order to get rid of thepin} 9. Bxd8 Nxd2 10. Kxd2 
Kxd8 $17 {with a better endgame for black - he has a space advantage and the pair of 
bishops} *

