1. d4 d5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. e3 c5 4. c3 {this is the Colle System, but after black's next 
two moves it will more likely than not transpose to the London System.} cxd4 5. exd4 
Bf5 $1 {it's important to prevent the development of the bishop to d3} 6. Qb3 Qc7 
{controlling f4 and black has an improved version of the London System since the Bc1 
cannot come to f4} 7. Bg5 e6 8. Bxf6 {trying to disturb the balance, but it works in 
black's favour.} gxf6 9. Nbd2 Nc6 10. Be2 Bh6 $1 {and the unopposed black-squared 
bishop is very strong. Black can even castle long and start attack along the g-file} 
*

