1. d4 d5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. e3 c5 4. Bd3 Nc6 5. O-O Bg4 6. c3 e6 7. Nbd2 {white adopts the 
development that black uses in the Semi-Slav.} Bd6 8. Qe2 O-O 9. dxc5 {playing for 
e4} Bxc5 10. e4 Bb6 {a nice waiting move, keeping the queen on d8 dissuades white 
from possible sacrifices on h7 as g5 is now covered by the queen from d8.} 11. h3 Bh5 
12. e5 $6 Nd7 {and white has trouble defending e5 when there is no sacrifice on h7 
followed by Ng5} *

